# Font Handling Rules

## Problem: Google Fonts Download Failures

**Symptoms:**
- `AbortError: The user aborted a request`
- `Failed to download 'Inter' from Google Fonts`
- `Failed to download 'Poppins' from Google Fonts`

## Solutions

### 1. Use Local Fonts Instead of Google Fonts

**File: [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx)**

```typescript
// ❌ Avoid Google Fonts
import { Inter, Poppins } from 'next/font/google'

// ✅ Use local fonts or system fonts
import localFont from 'next/font/local'

const inter = localFont({
  src: './fonts/Inter-Regular.woff2',
  fallback: ['system-ui', 'arial']
})

const poppins = localFont({
  src: './fonts/Poppins-Regular.woff2',
  fallback: ['system-ui', 'arial']
})
```

### 2. Implement Proper Fallback Strategy

**File: [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)**

```javascript
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      fontFamily: {
        sans: [
          'Inter',
          'system-ui',
          '-apple-system',
          'BlinkMacSystemFont',
          'Segoe UI',
          'Roboto',
          'sans-serif'
        ],
        display: [
          'Poppins',
          'system-ui',
          '-apple-system',
          'BlinkMacSystemFont',
          'Segoe UI',
          'Roboto',
          'sans-serif'
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 3. Error Handling for Font Loading

```typescript
// In layout.tsx
export default function RootLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode
}) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <head>
        {/* Fallback font loading */}
        <link
          rel="preconnect"
          href="https://fonts.googleapis.com"
          crossOrigin="anonymous"
        />
        <style jsx global>{`
          @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Poppins:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap');
          
          /* Fallback to system fonts if Google Fonts fail */
          body {
            font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
          }
          
          .font-display {
            font-family: 'Poppins', system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
          }
        `}</style>
      </head>
      <body className={inter.className}>
        {children}
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Font Loading Strategy
- **Primary**: Local fonts (most reliable)
- **Secondary**: Google Fonts with fallback
- **Fallback**: System fonts

### 2. Performance Optimization
```typescript
// Preload critical fonts
<link
  rel="preload"
  href="/fonts/Inter-Regular.woff2"
  as="font"
  type="font/woff2"
  crossOrigin="anonymous"
/>
```

### 3. Error Handling
```typescript
// Check if fonts loaded successfully
useEffect(() => {
  document.fonts.ready.then(() => {
    console.log('Fonts loaded successfully')
  }).catch(() => {
    console.warn('Font loading failed, using fallbacks')
  })
}, [])
```

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Download Local Font Files
- Download Inter and Poppins from Google Fonts
- Place in `public/fonts/` directory
- Use WOFF2 format for best performance

### 2. Update Layout Configuration
- Replace Google Fonts imports with local fonts
- Add proper fallback chains
- Implement error handling

### 3. Test Font Loading
- Test with network throttling
- Verify fallback fonts work
- Check performance impact

## Monitoring

### Font Loading Status
```typescript
// Add to layout for debugging
useEffect(() => {
  if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
    document.fonts.ready.then(() => {
      console.log('✅ Fonts loaded:', document.fonts.size)
    }).catch((error) => {
      console.warn('⚠️ Font loading error:', error)
    })
  }
}, [])
```

### Performance Metrics
- Monitor font loading time
- Check for layout shifts
- Verify fallback font usage
